  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Plant 10,000 Trees to Combat Climate Change</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Green Care Association plans to plant 10,000 bee-friendly, medicinal or fruit bearing native trees to combat desertification in Northwest Cameroon. These native forests will help combat climate change (and donors offset their own carbon footprints), preserve fertile land, and provide income to the local communities. Green Care works with local populations to teach tree management, water catchment protection, and income generating activities such as bee keeping and fruit harvesting.</narrative>
  </description>
